Introduction

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Base URL

http://localhost

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

POST api/login

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"vwbnrnukcwczz\",
    \"password\": \"\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "vwbnrnukcwczz",
    "password": ""
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST api/login

Body Parameters

email  string  

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters.

password  string  

Must be at least 8 characters.

GET api/logout

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/logout" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/logout"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (500):

GET api/admin/mails

Store a newly created resource in storage.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/admin/mails" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"smtp_host\": \"vitae\",
    \"smtp_port\": \"unde\",
    \"smtp_user\": \"blanditiis\",
    \"smtp_pass\": \"est\",
    \"from_email\": \"explicabo\",
    \"from_name\": \"esse\",
    \"email_encryption\": \"ducimus\",
    \"header_email\": \"pariatur\",
    \"is_smtp\": \"consequuntur\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/admin/mails"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "smtp_host": "vitae",
    "smtp_port": "unde",
    "smtp_user": "blanditiis",
    "smtp_pass": "est",
    "from_email": "explicabo",
    "from_name": "esse",
    "email_encryption": "ducimus",
    "header_email": "pariatur",
    "is_smtp": "consequuntur"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:
